stone for the sake of order.The case against the Earps, with its dueling narratives of brutality and justification, played out themes of betrayal, revenge, and even adultery. Attorney Thomas Fitch, one of the era's finest advocates, ultimately managed-against considerable odds-to save Earp from the gallows. But the case could easily have ended in a conviction, and Wyatt Earp would have been hanged or imprisoned, not celebrated as an American icon.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aFrontier and pioneer lifexArizonaxTombstone. 0aFrontier and pioneer lifezArizonazTombstone. 0aOutlawsxHistoryx19th centuryxArizonaxTombstone. 0aOutlawszArizonazTombstonexHistoryy19th century. 0aPeace officersxBiographyxArizonaxTombstone. 0aPeace officerszArizonazTombstonevBiography. 0aTrials (Murder)xArizonaxTombstone. 0aTrials (Murder)zArizonazTombstone. 0aViolencexHistoryx19th centuryxArizonaxTombstone. 0aViolencezArizonazTombstonexHistoryy19th century. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300129243423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300129243.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles